DN-004 \'97 32.768kHz RTC Crystal (XL1/XL2) The nRF52840 has two crystal inputs \'97 a mandatory 32MHz main clock on XC1/XC2 and an optional 32.768kHz low-frequency crystal on XL1/XL2 used for RTC timekeeping and accurate BLE low-power advertising. For v1 the 32.768kHz crystal is omitted. This device has no timekeeping requirement and BLE is not implemented in v1, so the internal RC oscillator is sufficient for basic sleep/wake timing. XL1 and XL2 are left as no-connect in the schematic. The crystal footprint will be added as DNP on the PCB for potential population in v2 when BLE and low-power sleep modes are implemented.\
